<recipe>
  <name>Tomato Aspic</name>
  <yield_count>4-6</yield_count>
  <yield_measure>servings</yield_measure>
  <notes>Any soup that contains a package of lemon jello is worth at least trying, no?</notes>
  <ingredients>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>1 small package</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>lemon Jello</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>1 cup</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>boiling water</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>pinch</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>salt</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>1 1/2 tbl</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>white vinegar</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity></quantity>
      <ingredient_name>onion juice</ingredient_name>
      <preparation>to taste (onion juice??)</preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity></quantity>
      <ingredient_name>tabasco</ingredient_name>
      <preparation>to taste</preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>6 oz can</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>tomato sauce*</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity></quantity>
      <ingredient_name>stuffed green olives</ingredient_name>
      <preparation>sliced (optional)</preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity></quantity>
      <ingredient_name>chopped celery (optional)</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity></quantity>
      <ingredient_name>chopped bell peppers (optional)</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity></quantity>
      <ingredient_name>small shrimp or crab (optional)</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
  </ingredients>
  <preparation>Disolve Jello in boiling water.  Add salt, vinegar, onion juice, Tabasco and tomato sauce*.  Chill to thicken and add any of the optional ingredients.  Chill to set.

* the prep and ingredients both listed a "6 oz. can of tomato sauce", though typically in that size its tomato paste.  Caveat preperator.</preparation>
